<title type="html"><![CDATA[4/24(Sun.) First woman of colour completes a solo expedition … &amp; Why people thought steel houses …? ( Host: Danny)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=611&amp;p=634#p634"><![CDATA[
4/24(Sun.) First woman of colour completes a solo expedition across Antarctica &amp; Why people thought steel houses were a good idea? ( Host: Danny)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br /><br />///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session1: First woman of colour completes a solo expedition across Antarctica (transcript included)</span><br /><a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/learningenglish/english/features/lingohack_2022/ep-220406" class="postlink">https://www.bbc.co.uk/learningenglish/english/features/lingohack_2022/ep-220406</a><br />1.What do you think after seeing the footage?<br />2.Have you tried to do something out of your comfort zone? What have you done? Or a toughest thing you have done.<br />3.What are those hardships and challenges in that?<br />4.Did you have to face any reservation from relatives or your community? Please share with us.<br /><br />Extra information:<br />What does “woman of colour” mean? Is that a racial pejorative? (No need to answer. But if you need an answer, you can reference information in wiki. ( <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Person_of_color">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Person_of_color</a><!-- m -->)<br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session2: Why people thought steel houses were a good 